parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To command, order, direct, bid. From a primary kello; 'hail'; to incite by word, i.e. Order.
A prolonged form of a primary stao stah'-o; to stand, used in various applications.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A chariot, vehicle. Probably from airo (as a particle of union) prefixed); a chariot (compare harmos).
Both (of two). Comparative of amphi; both.
From philos and hippos; fond of horses; Philippus, the name of four Israelites.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
From eune and echo; a castrated person; by extension an impotent or unmarried man; by implication, a chamberlain.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To go down, come down, either from the sky or from higher land, descend. From kata and the base of basis; to descend.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Water. And genitive case, hudatos, etc. From the base of huetos; water literally or figuratively.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: Lit: I dip, submerge, but specifically of ceremonial dipping; I baptize.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
